an and Native American history but also establishes a new context for understanding racism, colonialism, and the meaning of ethnicity in early America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEsclaves indiens d'AmériquexHistoirex17e sièclexÉtats-Unis (Sud). 0aEsclavesxCommercexHistoirex17e sièclexGrande-Bretagne. 0aEsclavesxCommercexHistoirex17e sièclexÉtats-Unis (Sud). 0aIndian slavesxHistoryx17th centuryxSouthern States. 0aIndian slaveszSouthern StatesxHistoryy17th century. 0aIndians of North AmericaxSocial conditionsxSouthern States. 0aIndians of North AmericazSouthern StatesxSocial conditions. 0aIndians, Treatment ofxHistoryx17th centuryxSouthern States. 0aIndians, Treatment ofzSouthern StatesxHistoryy17th century. 0aIndiens d'AmériquexConditions socialesxÉtats-Unis (Sud)xGreat BritainxSouthern States. 0aIndiens d'Amérique, Attitudes envers lesxHistoirex17e sièclexÉtats-Unis (Sud). 0aSlave tradexHistoryx17th centuryxGreat Britain. 0aSlave tradexHistoryx17th centuryxSouthern States. 0aSlave tradezGreat BritainxHistoryy17th century. 0aSlave tradezSouthern StatesxHistoryy17th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / Colonial Period (1600-1775).2bisacsh1 aNairne, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStewart, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013321940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300133219423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300133219/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles